4 Main Areas

Remote Repository          GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket
      │                    (team shares code here)
      │
      │ clone/fetch/pull
      ▼
Local Repository           .git folder
      │                    (full history stored here)
      │
      │ checkout
      ▼
Staging Area               .git/index file
      │                    (files ready to commit)
      │
      │ add
      ▼
Working Directory          your actual files
                           (what you see and edit)


---------------------------------------------------------

Full Day Example

# 1. Get repo from remote → working directory
git clone https://github.com/myorg/myrepo.git

# 2. Edit files in working directory
vim login.py

# 3. Move to staging area
git add login.py

# 4. Check what's staged
git status
# Changes to be committed:
#   modified: login.py       ← in staging ✅

# 5. Commit to local repo
git commit -m "fixed login bug"
# [main f4g5h6i] fixed login bug  ← in local repo ✅

# 6. Push to remote repo
git push origin main
# → github now has your commit ✅

# 7. Teammate pushes new code, you fetch
git fetch origin
# → downloads to local repo, not working dir

# 8. Merge into working directory
git merge origin/main
# → working dir updated ✅
-------------------------------------------------
Working Dir → Staging      git add filename
Staging     → Local Repo   git commit -m "message"
Local Repo  → Remote       git push origin main
Remote      → Local Repo   git fetch origin
Local Repo  → Working Dir  git checkout branch   ← switch
Local Repo  → Working Dir  git merge             ← combine
Remote      → Working Dir  git pull              ← fetch + merge
